description.narrative: (Rwanda): The Rwanda Health Systems Strengthening Activity (RHSSA) will continue to support innovations and build the capacity of the Government of Rwanda (GOR) to move from health systems support to health systems strengthening. RHSSA will develop and support the implementation of policies, strategies, and action plans for institutional strengthening at the central and decentralized level. Through this activity USAID will support the Community Based Health Insurance which contributes to the accessibility for all Rwandans to primary health care, including family planning services. RHSSA support health facilities in the district planning process with the approach of the quality improvement to integrate standards for improving RMNCH and family planning through the facility accreditation system at both secondary and primary health care. RHSSA will improve the wellbeing of Rwandans and safeguard USG investments in the health sector.
